'''Fujiwara no Taishi''' (藤原 泰子, also read '''Fujiwara no Yasuko'''; 1095–1156) was an [[Empress consort of Japan]]. She was the consort of [[Emperor Toba]] of Japan. Her birth name was '''Fujiwara no Kunshi''' (藤原 勲子), her ''[[ingō]]'' was '''Kaya-no-in''' (高陽院) and her [[dharma name]] upon [[bhikkuni|entering religious orders]] in 1141 was '''Shōjōri''' (清浄理).

==Notes==
{{reflist}}

==External links==
* http://www.guide2womenleaders.com/japan_heads.htm
