'''Fujiwara no Taishi''' (藤原 泰子, also read '''Fujiwara no Yasuko'''; 1095–1156) was an [[Empress consort of Japan]]. She was the consort of [[Emperor Toba]] of Japan. Her birth name was '''Fujiwara no Kunshi''' (藤原 勲子), her ''[[ingō]]'' was '''Kaya-no-in''' (高陽院) and her [[:en:Dharma name|Dharma name]] upon [[:en:bhikkuni|entering religious orders]] in 1141 was '''Shōjōri''' (清浄理).
